Ordered half BBQ chicken, half cheese pie.  I wanted the half without the BBQ chicken first, and the slice I ate tasted like a $.99 slice (as stated in another review).  One slice had a piece of the BBQ chicken, and it was flavorful, but another participant of this "pizza consuming activity" stated that if it was not for the BBQ sauce, the pizza would have no taste.  I told him, look at what I have to contend with (considering I had no BBQ sauce on the majority of my bread-sauce-cheese product).  This is NYC, and pizza should be better.  Oh, and my $19.00 "entree" did not come with plates or napkins.  Pitiful.  Update: 07/15/2019  So apparently it's been 4 years since I was there last, and I forgot about the pizza.  I went there again to get 2 cheese slices.  The slices came with a pound of cheese oozing everywhere; yuck!  The sauce had no flavor, and the crust was not Brooklyn  (not too thin and not too thick, with a slightly crispy bottom).  When I went to post a review, I saw the review I already did 4 years ago.  I should have Googled my own review and left this place for the tourists. LOL

I’m very surprised to see some negative reviews on here. I’ve been ordering from Pronto via Seamless for roughly six months or so now. It’s my go to Italian spot in Brooklyn Heights! I am obsessed with Pronto Pizza. It’s my favorite pizza spot in Brooklyn hands down. I order from here when I’m at work. I can sincerely say I’ve never been disappointed. Their pan pizza is incredible. Their penne vodka is amazing—that’s my favorite dish from here. It could easily feed 3 people—The portions are HUGE, and the food is always fresh and tasty. They also listen to your special instructions and are extremely fast with delivery. Delivery guys are always pleasant and very friendly! Prices are fantastic. I love this place so much.

Pronto pizza sure is pronto. (Not sarcastic.) Stopped by on a whim when I saw their sign for 2 slices and a drink for $5.50. Basically a steal and I was so hungry.  This place is oddly structured - it's super narrow between the barstools on the wall and the counter, so if anyone is waiting on food, you're in the way. I was ordering but insanely overwhelmed because I literally just walked in, the guy says next PRONTO and all of a sudden I'm next, and the lady in front of me is standing in front of the counter (because she can't move) and I can't even see what's available.  Anyway, once you get past that, the pizza is good and it's a good deal. There's honestly a decent amount of seating as well so that's nice.  I'd go back, but I'd stick to a cheese slice so I don't have to rush and choose and have buyers remorse if I don't like it.
